      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the median house price in West End?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "West End's median house price is approximately $1.8 million to $2 million as of early 2026. West End's strong lifestyle credentials, walkable CBD proximity and limited housing supply underpin consistent demand from professionals and families seeking inner-city character living."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What makes West End attractive to buyers?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "West End offers a rare combination of walkable inner-city lifestyle, independent café culture on Boundary Street, direct access to South Bank and the river, and a strong sense of community identity. Buyers are typically professionals and couples seeking inner-city proximity with more character than a CBD apartment provides."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is West End a good suburb to sell in?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "West End's proximity to the CBD, its established lifestyle reputation and limited land supply make it a strong selling environment. The suburb's appeal to both owner-occupiers and investors provides a broad buyer pool that supports competitive sale conditions."
      }
    }
  ]
